LeetCode 14: Longest Common Prefix returns the longest common starting substring across all strings in strs, or "" if none. 

Java solution uses efficient vertical scanning.
​
Java Implementation

#Horizontal scan variant (intuitive)
class Solution {
    public String longestCommonPrefix(String[] strs) {
        if (strs == null || strs.length == 0) return "";
        String prefix = strs[0];
        for (int i = 1; i < strs.length; i++) {
            while (strs[i].indexOf(prefix) != 0) {
                prefix = prefix.substring(0, prefix.length() - 1);
                if (prefix.isEmpty()) return "";
            }
        }
        return prefix;
    }
}

Note:
Horizontal scan variant (intuitive): Shrink prefix until it matches start of ALL strings. O(S) time where S=sum lengths.
​
​

#Vertical scan alt (optimal):

public String longestCommonPrefix(String[] strs) {
    if (strs.length == 0) return "";
    for (int i = 0; i < strs[0].length(); i++) {
        char c = strs[0].charAt(i);
        for (int j = 1; j < strs.length; j++) {
            if (i == strs[j].length() || strs[j].charAt(i) != c) {
                return strs[0].substring(0, i);
            }
        }
    }
    return strs[0];
}

#Step-by-Step Logic
Guard: Handle null/empty strs → "".
Candidate: prefix = strs[0].
Validate each string: For strs[i] (i≥1):
While prefix not at start of strs[i] (via indexOf or char check):
Shrink prefix by 1 char.
If empty, return "".
Return final prefix.
​
​

#Thought Process
Intuition: Common prefix is min length where chars match position-by-position across ALL strings.
Horizontal: Start with first, iteratively trim until fits all (easy debug).
Vertical: Check column i before i+1 (early exit). Both O(S), but vertical scans less.
Edge-first: Sorting + compare extremes O(S log n) - clever but log factor.
Why shrink? Guarantees prefix never exceeds true common length.
​

#Edge Cases
Empty/null array: []/null → "".
Empty string: ["", "abc"] → "".
Single string: ["abc"] → "abc".
No prefix: ["dog","cat"] → "" pos 0 mismatch.
Shortest limits: ["flow","flower"] → "flow".
All same: ["prefix","prefix"] → "prefix".​
Max 200×200: Linear fine.
